Business Case Instances are individual iterations of a Business Case definition. Once a Business Case has been started, it becomes a unique Business Case Instance that can be worked on and advanced in order to complete the workflow.

This article takes a closer look at Business Case Instances, exploring how they are created, managed, and used within the Workplace 2 environment.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Business Case Instances
Business Case Instances are collected in a table view in the Business Case Instances tab. It consists of two main areas:

- Top **toolbar** with search filters and bulk action buttons (only visible when at least one checkbox is selected)

- **Table** overview containing all Business Case Instances

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The following actions can be performed on a Business Case Instance from the Business Case Instances tab, depending on its current status:

- **Continue**: Opens the Business Case Instance at its currently open task

- **Assign**: Reassigns the Business Case Instance to a different user

- **Terminate**: Terminates the Business Case Instance

- **Delete**: Deletes the Business Case Instance

> Tip: Perform actions from the details page

All actions which can be performed from one of the table overviews of Workplace 2 are also available in the details page.

The table in the Business Case Instances tab contains the following information:

Field

Description

**State**

Status of the Business Case Instance:

- ![](data:image/png;base64,) **Created**: The Business Case has been started, but no task has been generated for this Business Case Instance yet.

- ![](data:image/png;base64,) **Started**: The first task in the Business Case Instance has been generated.

- ![](data:image/png;base64,) **Finished**: All tasks in the Business Case Instance have the status **Finished**.

- ![](data:image/png;base64,) **Failed**: The execution has failed due to a backend error and the Business Case Instance cant continue automatically.

- ![](data:image/png;base64,) **Terminated**: The Business Case Instance has been terminated by a user.

**ID**

Unique ID of the Business Case Instance

**Started at**

Starting time of the Business Case Instance

**Business Case Name**

Name of the Business Case from which the Business Case Instance was started

**Business Case ID**

Unique ID of the Business Case

**Started by**

Name of the user who started the Business Case

**Task ID**

Unique ID of the currently open task in the Business Case Instance

> Tip: Configure table columns

To display or hide specific columns from the table, click the three-dot icon in the right corner of the header row and select or deselect the desired columns.

## Find a Business Case Instance
Each Business Case Instance can be located individually through its **Business Case Instance ID**.

To locate a specific Business Case Instance, navigate to the **Business Case Instances tab**. This tab displays all Business Case Instances in a fully searchable and sortable table view.

The table contents can be refined using the following filters:

![tab_ business case instances_search.png](data:image/png;base64,)

- **Free-text search** for the fields **Business Case Name** and **Started by**

- **State**

- **User**

- **Business Case**

- **Started at**

## Start a new Business Case Instance
To start a new Business Case Instance, locate the desired Business Case and click **Start** in the tile body. The Business Case is immediately instantiated in the background by Process Engine and the task editor is opened at the first Human Task in the workflow.

## Continue a Business Case Instance
- Navigate to the Business Case Instances tab and search for the desired Business Case Instance using the search bar and filters.

- Click the status icon of the Business Case Instance. A snackbar with action buttons is displayed.![Snackbar with buttons for actions: Continue, Assign, Terminate, and Delete.](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Continue** to reopen the Business Case Instance. The task editor is opened at the current Human Task.

## Terminate a Business Case Instance
Terminating a Business Case Instance cancels the entire workflow. All information about the Business Case Instance and its Human Tasks is kept in the system and can be viewed in Workplace 2. However, the Business Case Instance can no longer be reopened and advanced in the task editor.

Terminating a Business Case Instance can be done in one of the following ways:

- Through the **snackbar in the Business Case Instances tab**

Navigate to the Business Case Instances tab and search for the desired Business Case Instance using the search bar and filters.

- Click the status icon of the Business Case Instance. A snackbar with action buttons is displayed.![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Terminate** and confirm the action.

- With **action buttons in the details page** of the Business Case Instance

Navigate to the details page of the Business Case Instance.

- Click **Terminate** at the top of the details page and confirm the action.

- From within the **task editor** of the Business Case Instance

Open the Business Case Instance. The task editor is opened.

- Click **Cancel** in the left navigation panel and confirm the action. The Business Case Instance is immediately terminated.

## Delete a Business Case Instance
Unlike the Terminate action, the Delete action removes the entire workflow entry from the Business Case Instances table.

> Irreversible action

Deleting a Business Case Instance is an irreversible action. Once a Business Case Instance has been deleted, it will no longer be displayed in the table of the Business Case Instances tab, and its details page will be inaccessible through the direct URL.

Deleting a Business Case Instance can be done in one of the following ways:

- Navigate to the Business Case Instances tab and click the status icon of the Business Case Instance you want to delete. A snackbar with action buttons is opened. Click **Delete** and confirm the action.

- Open the details page of the Business Case Instance you want to delete. Click the **Delete** button at the top of the page and confirm the action.

## View the details of a Business Case Instance
The details page of a Business Case displays information about the Business Case and action buttons to manage it. You can access it in one of the following ways:

- **Click the Business Case Instance ID** in the Business Case Instances tab

- **Open the URL** of the Business Case

> Tip: How to get the URL of a Business Case Instance

Every Workplace item can be accessed through a unique URL that leads to its details page. To copy the URL, open the details panel of the desired item and click the **Copy link** button.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The details page of a Business Case Instance contains the following information:

Field

Description

**State**

Status of the Business Case Instance

**Business Case**

Name of the Business Case from which the Business Case Instance was opened

**Tasks**

List of all tasks within the Business Case Instance (the current step is highlighted in bold)

> Tip: View all tasks in a Business Case Instance

Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) **See full tasks progress regarding this Business Case Instance** to open the Tasks tab with the filter **Business Case ID** automatically set to the ID of this Business Case Instance.

**Current Assignee**

Username of the assignee of the current task

**Potential Assignee**

Username(s) of potential assignee(s)

**Summary**

Short description of the Business Case (optional)

**Full Description**

Full description of the Business Case (optional)

**Started by**

Username of the creator of the Business Case Instance

**Started at**

Date and time of start

**Last updated at**

Date and time of the latest update of the Business Case Instance

**Business Case ID**

Unique ID of the Business Case from which the Business Case Instance was started

**Current Task ID**

Unique ID of the current step in the Business Case Instance

The following actions can be performed on a Business Case Instance from its details page:

- **Continue**: Opens the Business Case Instance at its currently open task

- **Assign**: Assigns the Business Case Instance to a user

- **Terminate**: Terminates the Business Case Instance

- **Delete**: Deletes the Business Case Instance

- **Copy link**: Copies the URL of the Business Case Instance to the clipboard
